      "source": [
        "## Exploratory Data Analysis\n",
        "\n",
        "Before constructing the Monte Carlo model, it is useful to examine how the selected stocks behaved during the historical period.\n",
        "\n",
        "Because the stocks have very different price levels, comparing their raw prices directly is not particularly informative. Instead, each stock is normalized to start at a value of 100 at the beginning of the observation period.\n",
        "\n",
        "This allows us to compare their relative performance over time and identify differences in growth and volatility.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "5181e161",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
            "image/png": "",
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 1200x600 with 1 Axes>"
