      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "fd968732",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Estimating Historical Returns and Volatility\n",
        "\n",
        "Monte Carlo simulation requires estimates of the statistical characteristics of each stock.\n",
        "\n",
        "For each company, daily returns are calculated from the adjusted closing prices. Using these returns, two key quantities are estimated:\n",
        "\n",
        "* Mean daily return, which represents the average daily growth observed during the training period.\n",
        "* Daily volatility (standard deviation), which measures the variability of returns and serves as a proxy for risk.\n",
        "\n",
        "These estimates will be used as parameters for the probability distributions from which future returns are simulated.\n"
      ]
    },
