      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "9e97a2f0",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Constructing Prediction Intervals\n",
        "\n",
        "The simulated price paths can be summarized using prediction intervals.\n",
        "\n",
        "For each stock, the 5th percentile and 95th percentile of the simulated final prices are calculated. Together, these values form a 90% prediction interval.\n",
        "\n",
        "If the model accurately captures the uncertainty of future stock prices, the realized stock price should frequently fall within this interval.\n",
        "\n",
        "These intervals will later be compared with the actual stock prices observed one year later.\n"
      ]
    },
