      "source": [
        "## Collecting the Realized Stock Prices\n",
        "\n",
        "The Monte Carlo model has generated prediction intervals based exclusively on historical information available between April 2024 and April 2025.\n",
        "\n",
        "To evaluate the model, we now collect the stock prices that actually occurred during the following year (April 2025 to April 2026).\n",
        "\n",
        "Rather than comparing the simulations with a single trading day, the realized price will be defined as the average closing price during the final trading week of the evaluation period. This reduces the impact of short-term market fluctuations and provides a more stable measure of the stock's realized value.\n"
      ]
    },
