        "### Results of the Percentile Analysis\n",
        "\n",
        "The percentile analysis suggests that the realized stock prices generally occurred within plausible regions of their respective simulated distributions.\n",
        "\n",
        "The percentile ranks ranged from approximately 27% to 87%, indicating that none of the realized outcomes occurred near the extreme tails of the simulated distributions. This suggests that the Monte Carlo model was able to generate distributions that were broadly consistent with the observed future stock prices.\n",
        "\n",
        "Particularly notable is Walmart, whose realized price corresponded almost exactly to the 50th percentile of the simulated distribution. Microsoft and Exxon Mobil produced higher percentile ranks, indicating that their realized performance was stronger than the model typically expected, although still well within the range of simulated outcomes.\n",
        "\n",
        "Overall, the percentile analysis provides additional evidence that the model produced realistic distributions of future prices rather than merely capturing realized outcomes through excessively wide prediction intervals.\n"
      ]
